INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(146, 2, '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '<h1>Paraplegia Injury</h1>\nIf you are a victim of an accident that results in paraplegia, an experienced personal injury attorney can represent you in court and help you receive appropriate compensation for your damages. Paraplegia can be a devastating outcome of a spinal cord injury and many people never fully recover. The Law Office of David Azizi specializes in paraplegia injury and spinal injury cases. We have helped many clients receive the support and compensation they deserve so that they can lead a comfortable and healthy lifestyle after their traumatic experience.\n\n<h3>Common Causes of Paraplegia </h3>\n\nParaplegia is a lower injury that affects the legs and lower parts of the body. The injury can result in complete loss of sensation in the lower body, and the inability to move certain limbs and muscles. More serious cases result in loss of bladder control and improper bowel functioning, and these serious conditions rarely improve over the course of the victim’s life. Any excessive damage to the spinal cord can lead to paraplegia. The common accidents that cause paraplegia are:\nAuto accidents\nMotorcycle or bike accidents\nDiving injuries\nSporting accidents\nPedestrian accidents\nConstruction accidents\n\nThe medical expenses that result from paraplegia can be a financial burden for most individuals and their families.\n\n<h3>Working with a Paraplegia Attorney </h3>\n\nThe professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com have extensive experience in paraplegia injuries and accidents that result in spinal cord injuries. We will do everything legally possible to aggressively pursue your case to obtain the maximum recovery you deserve. We understand how difficult it can be to work with insurance companies who will only agree to pay a very small portion of your medical expenses. Most people simply cannot afford to manage these exorbitant costs on their own, and must resort to personal loans, credit cards and other financial resources just to pay their medical bills.\n\nOur experienced legal professionals will take the time to investigate your case, contact witnesses from the accident, work with medical professionals to assess your condition, and build a solid case for a claim or lawsuit.\n\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can provide you with immediate assistance. We will not charge you any fees until your case is resolved.', 'Paraplegia Injuries', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'paraplegia-injuries', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=146', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(148, 2, '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '<h1>Pedestrian Accidents</h1>\nPedestrian accidents are some of the most common cases involved in our cities, and most are the result of driver negligence and failure to observe the pedestrian right-of-way. If you are involved in a pedestrian accident that results in hospitalization or severe injuries, you will need the assistance of a personal injury lawyer to represent your case. The Law Office of David Azizi has extensive experience in handling pedestrian accident cases and will take the time to evaluate the damages, gather testimonies from witnesses and even reconstruct the scene of the accident in order to pursue your case vigorously.\n\n<h3>Understanding Pedestrian Accidents </h3>\n\nSituations that may be defined as a pedestrian accident include:\nBeing struck by a car\nBeing hit by a bus\nBeing struck by a truck or motorcycle\nPoor property maintenance that results in a fall\nTending to a crash on the interstate, highway or road\n\n<h3>What to Do When You are Involved in a Pedestrian Accident </h3>\n\nIn some cases, it can be difficult to assess whether the pedestrian accident was the result of somebody else’s negligence or the pedestrian’s own fault. No matter what the circumstance may be, it is important that you:\nContact the police department to report the accident\nStay at the scene of the accident until help arrives\nObtain any names and phone numbers of witnesses at the scene\nCall an experienced personal injury attorney from AziziPersonalInjury.com as soon as possible to report the event\n\nBeing involved in a pedestrian accident can be a very distressing experience, and you may not have the resources or energy to return to work and pay your medical bills.\n\n<h3>Work with an Experienced Pedestrian Accident Attorney </h3>\n\nAziziPersonalInjury.com has the experience and knowledge to litigate pedestrian accident cases. We understand how challenging it can be to work with insurance companies that want a quick settlement and do not take your short-term and long-term interests into account. We make sure we do everything possible to cover all of the details of the case and help you receive full compensation for all expenses related to the incident.\n\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can discuss your case. AziziPersonalInjury.com is determined to aggressively pursue your case, and we will not charge you a single dollar until the matter is fully resolved.', 'Pedestrian Accidents', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pedestrian-accidents', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=148', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(150, 2, '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '<h1>Quadriplegia Injury</h1>\nOne of the most tragic and physically devastating injuries someone can endure is a quadriplegia injury. Quadriplegia injuries can result in a lifetime of pain and discomfort as the victim loses all sensation and the ability to move their four limbs. If you or a loved one have become quadriplegic as a result of an accident or negligence, you will need the assistance of an experienced quadriplegia attorney to handle your case. The professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com have extensive experience in representing quadriplegia cases, and can provide guidance and support when you need to file a claim or lawsuit.\n\n<h3>Common Causes of Quadriplegia </h3>\n\nQuadriplegia is also known as ‘tetraplegia’, and is the complete paralysis of all four limbs as a result of severe spinal damage. Serious cases rarely improve over time, and the victim typically needs extensive medical care and attention throughout the course of his or her life. Excessive damage to the spinal cord can be a result of several types of accidents and injuries such as:\nAutomobile accidents\nConstruction or on-the-job incidents\nMotorcycle or biking accidents\nSporting accidents\nDefective products\n\nThe medical expenses and rehabilitative care involved with taking care of a quadriplegic can put a financial strain on any family or victim. Working with an experienced quadriplegia lawyer from the Law Office of David Azizi means you can count on professional legal representation to recover compensation for your damages which you deserve.\n\n<h3>Working with a Quadriplegia Attorney </h3>\n\nWe have extensive experience in representing clients involved in personal injury cases and specialize in injuries related to spinal cord damage. We will do everything legally possible to aggressively pursue your case and to ensure that you and your family are not taken advantage of by insurance companies and medical providers.\n\nYou don’t have to resort to personal loans, credit cards or other financial resources just to cover the cost of medical bills; allow our quadriplegia attorneys to assess your case and assist you with receiving adequate and fair compensation for your damages.\n\nAt AziziPersonalInjury.com, we take the time to investigate your case and aggressively litigate your claim order to build a solid case against the offending party. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can determine the best course of action for your quadriplegia case. We will not charge you a single dollar until your case is resolved.', 'Quadriplegia Injuries', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'quadriplegia-injuries', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=150', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(152, 2, '2013-04-30 06:58:16', '2013-04-30 06:58:16', '<h1>Azizi Personal Injury Can Handle Your Los Angeles Slip and Fall Accident Case</h1>\nSlip and fall accidents are common and include not only injury-causing tumbles on wet or uneven floors, but falls from scaffolds and staircases and other elevated places. Many of these accidents result in serious injury, especially to the back, and there can be costly, long-lasting effects. If the spinal cord or head is injured, the consequences can be even worse, and a personal injury lawyer dedicated to making sure your case is presented strongly can help you recover more than the insurance company is likely to offer.\n\nWhile your immediate concern after being hurt in a slip-and-fall accident should be receiving all the proper medical care to treat your injuries, you should contact us for a free consultation as soon as you can. After discussing your case, we can determine if negligence contributed to your accident and, since we work on a contingency basis, if we take your case, there is never any charge to you until the matter is fully resolved.\n\nWe have the experience and determination to fully investigate your case, and we are always willing to see it through to the end in court. The insurance company will try to get a quick settlement that only takes its own interests into account, but we know that your health and prosperity is all that matters. Instead of ignoring long-term consequences, we''ll make sure that you receive full compensation for both current and future expenses and loss of income your accident may have caused.\n\nPlease contact us today at (800) 991-LAW2 for a free consultation where your case can be discussed in privacy and without obligation or any stress. We know how to present your case in the strongest possible way, and we''ll make sure that your pain, suffering, and that all your medical and work-related needs and expenses are included in your settlement.', 'Slip and Fall', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slip-and-fall', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:58:16', '2013-04-30 06:58:16', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=152', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(154, 2, '2013-04-30 06:59:45', '2013-04-30 06:59:45', '<h1>Spinal Cord Injury</h1>\nA spinal cord injury can be a physically, emotionally and financially devastating experience. Victims of a spinal injury often suffer from the side effects of the injury for years, even decades, and the financial burden of ongoing medical expenses, the inability to work, and the responsibility to pay for physical rehabilitation can be stressful. The Law Office of David Aziz can reduce the stress of handling spinal cord injuries by developing a strong case against the negligent party. We have extensive experience in personal injury law, and are dedicated to making sure you receive the full compensation you deserve.\n\n<h3>Types of Spinal Cord Injuries </h3>\n\nSpinal cord injuries typically take the form of a herniated disc in the spinal column, thoracic injuries and central cord syndrome. Most back injuries are the result of an auto accident, truck crash a construction accident where the victim’s back bones become separated or in more severe cases, broken. The most common types of spinal cord injuries include:\nHerniated disc injuries – also known as a bulging disc or ruptured disc, this type of spinal cord injury typically occurs when the small bone connected to the spine separates the human back bones and creates pressure on the spinal column. The effects of this type of injury include shoulder pain, leg pain and lower back pain.\nThoracic injuries – these injuries are sustained in the abdominal muscle area and result in paraplegia. This means the individual typically cannot move their legs or feet as a result of the violent impact to the spine.\nCentral cord syndrome - this is an incomplete spinal cord injury that results in the impairment of the arms and hands. The damage typically occurs in the upper regions of the spinal cord and often leads to extensive sensory loss.\n\nA spinal cord injury can be serious and even life threatening. If you were involved in an accident that caused injury to your spine, contact the Law Offices of David Azizi so that we may provide a free evaluation of your claim.\n\n<h3>Working with a Spinal Cord Injury Lawyer </h3>\n\nAziziPersonalInjury.com has extensive experience in litigating spinal cord injury cases. We can help you recover appropriate compensation for your damages which you deserve that were caused by the traumatic event. Unfortunately, many insurance companies will try to reduce the gravity of the situation and reach a quick settlement; however, this does not take your best interests into account, and you may end up paying far more out-of-pocket expenses than you should.\n\nOur firm is dedicated to making sure you receive adequate compensation for your damages related to your spinal cord injury case. We will litigate your case using all of our resources and years of expertise in the field. We will determine your actual medical condition, find out how long your injuries will cause pain and suffering, and determine what your work-related needs and expenses may be. These details will need to be included in your settlement, and you can count on us to help you every step of the way.\n\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation and find out how we can help you receive the full compensation you deserve from your spinal injury case.', 'Spinal Cord Injuries', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'spinal-cord-injuries', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:59:45', '2013-04-30 06:59:45', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=154', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(156, 2, '2013-04-30 07:00:50', '2013-04-30 07:00:50', '<h1>Train Accidents</h1>\nIf you have been involved in a railroad crossing accident, a train crash or automobile-train collision, you will need the assistance of a train accident lawyer to represent you in your case. Train transportation continues to be one of the most popular methods of transportation and shipping, especially in Los Angeles and the surrounding community. However, California train accidents have become more common as more people turn to commuter rails and other types of trains for daily transportation.\n\nPersonal injury lawyers from AziziPersonalInjury.com have extensive experience in representing clients that have suffered from train accidents and injuries that result from a train crash.\n\n<h3>Common Causes of Train Accidents </h3>\n\nThe most common causes of train accidents include:\nDerailments\nTrain collisions with other trains\nTrain collisions with cars\nTrain collisions with pedestrians\nOn-board accidents\nMechanical failure\n\nThe accident may also be the result of several events such as driver negligence, unmarked railway crossings, poorly maintained railway equipment or driver fatigue. However, all trains are governed by State laws and you will need formal legal representation.\n\n<h3>Common Injuries Sustained from a Train Accident </h3>\n\nA personal injury lawyer can help you receive compensation for damages as a result of injuries from the accident. The most common injuries that occur from a train accident include:\nBrain injury\nSpinal cord injuries\nJoint or muscle pain that requres medical care/rehabilitation\nMigraines and headaches\nBurn injuries\n\n<h3>Working with a Train Accident Lawyer </h3>\n\nAn experienced train accident lawyer from AziziPersonalInjury.com will determine the scope of your case and outline all damages incurred both directly and indirectly from the accident. Train accident lawyers at AziziPersonalInjury.com will litigate your case against the negligent parties to help you receive the compensation you deserve.\n\nHigh speed train accidents can be tragic or lead to serious injuries, and you will need the assistance of a professional law firm to represent you when you pursue compensation for damages. No matter what type of accident you have been involved in, it is in your best interest to work with the experienced team of professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com to litigate the case against the offending parties.\n\nContact the professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com today for a free, no obligation consultation.', 'Train Accidents', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'train-accidents', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:00:50', '2013-04-30 07:00:50', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=156', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(158, 2, '2013-04-30 07:01:38', '2013-04-30 07:01:38', '<h1>Truck Accidents</h1>\nHave you or a loved one been a victim of a truck accident? Truck accidents can occur at any time and often result in serious injuries or in some cases, wrongful death. If you have been struck by a truck as a motorist or pedestrian, you may also be able to file a lawsuit or claim against the negligent truck driver.\n\nThe Law Office of David Azizi has extensive experience in representing clients involved in truck accident cases. We can help you receive appropriate compensation for your damages to cover medical expenses and other injury-related expenses incurred.\n\n<h3>When to Contact a Truck Accident Attorney </h3>\n\nContacting a truck accident attorney as soon as possible is the best course of action, because this allows the attorney to start investigating the case and gather essential details and evidence immediately after the accident. Common truck accidents include:\nBig rig crashes\nManufacturer defects in trucking equipment\nSemi and car collisions\nTractor-trailer wrecks\nTruck and vehicle collisions\nTruck and property collisions\nPedestrian being hit by a truck\n\n<h3>Working with a Truck Accident Lawyer </h3>\n\nThe Law Office of David Azizi has provided professional legal representation to help clients file a claim or a lawsuit against the offending party after a truck accident. We understand the extent of damages involved with serious truck accidents and have years of experience in the field of personal injury; you can count on us to help you recover appropriate compensation for your injuries.\n\nOur dedicated team is committed to helping you win your case. We will not charge you any fees for the consultation or for our services until the case is resolved. Contact us today to for a free, no obligation consultation.', 'Truck Accidents', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'truck-accidents', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:01:38', '2013-04-30 07:01:38', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=158', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(160, 2, '2013-04-30 07:02:29', '2013-04-30 07:02:29', '<h1>Vehicle Rollovers</h1>\nIf you were involved in a vehicle rollover accident, you need the assistance of an experienced personal injury attorney who can fight for your legal rights and assure you are compensated for your damages. Vehicle rollovers can be a devastating event that is usually the result of inattentive driving, speeding or manufacturer defects. The Law Office of David Aziz is dedicated to providing you with the best services you need for your rollover accident, and will take every step necessary to build a solid case.\n\n<h3>Common Injuries Sustained from Vehicle Rollovers </h3>\n\nCommon injuries sustained as a result of a vehicle rollover are:\nBrain injury\nBurn injury\nSpinal cord injuries\nBroken bones\n\nAfter receiving a full medical evaluation and treatment from a physician, you should contact a personal injury lawyer from AziziPersonalInjury.com immediately so we can start reviewing your case. The sooner that our lawyers can get involved with your case, the easier it will be to obtain appropriate compensation for your case.\n\n<h3>Vehicle Rollovers as a Result of Product Defects </h3>\n\nIn situations when the vehicle rollover is the fault of a manufacturer, our personal injury lawyers will pursue a claim on your behalf for manufacturer negligence. All manufacturers owe a duty to consumers to take certain steps to guard against injury. If your vehicle rollover accident was the result of a defective product, we can represent your case to help you recover all necessary damages.\n\n<h3>Working with a Personal Injury Attorney after a Vehicle Rollover Accident </h3>\n\nVehicle rollovers can results in fairly extensive and serious injuries. As such, it is important to get in touch with a personal injury lawyer as soon as possible. Insurance companies involved with your claim are not always looking out for your best interests and will want to settle the case as quickly as possible.\n\nOur firm is committed to providing you with superior services if you have suffered from personal injuries that are taking their toll on your finances, your physical and emotional health. At AziziPersonalInjury.com, we do everything possible to calculate lost wages and future income for compensation, and recover the costs of medical bills related to the rollover accident.', 'Vehicle Rollovers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'vehicle-rollovers', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:02:29', '2013-04-30 07:02:29', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=160', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(162, 2, '2013-04-30 07:03:52', '2013-04-30 07:03:52', '<h1>Wrongful Death</h1>\nWhenever someone close to us dies we naturally feel sad and upset. When that person is lost to us because of some person''s or group''s negligence, misconduct, or carelessness, our distress is even greater. Knowing that the death wasn''t necessary, that someone''s actions or inactions caused it, produces what is called a wrongful death.\n\nThe next of kin or surviving family may file a wrongful death lawsuit if they believe the death resulted from negligence, misconduct, or carelessness. Cases like this are tragically common and can arise from a variety of causes. Some of these include unnecessary exposure to harmful substances such as asbestos, reactions to Vioxx® and other medications, malpractice or other negligence on the part of medical professionals, automobile accidents that are caused by careless or reckless driving, including drunk drivers, and deaths that are caused by defective products that the manufacturer knew about or should have been aware of.\n\n<h3>What is Meant By “Wrongful Death?”</h3>\n\nA variety of cases and deaths can be considered as a wrongful death. In essence, a wrongful death is one that is unnecessary and that only occurred because of someone''s negligence, misconduct, carelessness, or by their actions. A wrongful death can come about instantly, such as during a motor vehicle accident, or slowly, like after exposure to asbestos.\n\n<h3>What Are Some Examples of Wrongful Death?</h3>\n\nRecently, there have been an increasing number of deaths from mesothelioma, a result of asbestos exposure. This exposure can result from manufacturers who can be shown to be negligent or from companies that fail to notify their workers about the presence of asbestos and do not provide adequate protection against it.\n\nAnd it isn''t just asbestos. People needlessly die after being exposed to Benzene. Exposure to the fumes that come from welding rods can also be a killer, and carelessness or negligence on the part of companies who make these products or groups who use them can also result in a wrongful death.\n\nDrug companies, too, can be liable for those who were killed by using their products, even if the product was used as directed. Merck, the manufacturer of Vioxx®, has been found responsible for deaths that came about because of side-effects of that drug, and other similar drugs have also been found to cause fatalities.\n\n<h3>What Can I Do If I Believe a Loved One Has Suffered a Wrongful Death?</h3>\n\nThose who remain after a family member has died from a wrongful death naturally feel frustrated and entitled to compensation. The loss of a loved one is always a very stressful time, and if that death was unnecessary and caused by others or another person, the feelings are even more pronounced. The death can create not only sadness and dismay, but serious financial consequences if the person who dies was the one whose income sustained the family.\n\nWhether the death resulted from exposure, a car accident, side effects from medicines, malpractice, or any one of a number of equally tragic conditions, the remaining members of the family may be entitled to receive compensation for their needless and drastic loss.\n\nIf you believe the death of a family member was the result of a wrongful death, you should contact AziziPersonalInjury.com for an experienced personal injury lawyer who can provide action equal to his caring. Expert, qualified legal representation and assistance can help you receive just compensation for your loss, and your taking that action helps overcome your sense of helplessness. An initial consultation where we can discuss your case, which we provide at no cost or obligation, will let you know if you have grounds for legal redress and compensation and how we can best provide assistance.\n\nOur experience with similar cases gives us an advantage over some other personal injury lawyers. We know how to build and present a solid case that will give you the highest possible settlement, one that includes acknowledgment of your grief, pain and suffering, and financial consequences.\n\nWe can make sure that your loss is not any greater than it needs to be and that your unnecessary and deep pain, anguish, and loss is acknowledged and fully addressed. Nothing can replace the lost person or undo the needless death, but we can make sure your suffering stops there.', 'Wrongful Death', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'wrongful-death', '', '', '2013-04-30 07:03:52', '2013-04-30 07:03:52', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=162', 0, 'page', '', 0);
